With few days to Eid-el-Fitr, Sokoto State governor, Aminu Tambuwal has approved the payment of advance salary to all categories of civil servants in the state to enable them celebrate with their families and loved ones. Tambuwal further reassured that his government will continue to embark on policies and programmes that will be beneficial to the people. A statement by the governor’s senior special assistant (SSA) on Media and Public Affairs, Abdullahi Danko, quoted the state commissioner for Finance, Alhaji Saidu Umar, as saying the advance payment will, however, be paid back in three tranches. “The advance salary to be paid to workers will, however, be deducted within three months beginning from the end of this month,” he said